stage.name: new
stage.narrative:
Clean Up Page
This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some finalisation (or "cleanup") tasks as your business object is closed down.
The cleanup action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after closing your business object at the end of a business process.
You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than before the disposal of the business object.

stage.name: new
stage.narrative:
Initialise Page
This is an optional page where you might choose to perform some initialisation tasks after your business object is loaded.
The initialise action will be called automatically by Automate immediately after loading your business object.
You will not be able to call this action from a business process, nor will it be called at any other time than after the creation of the object.

stage.name: Open
stage.code:
Success = False Message = ""
If moConnection Is Nothing Then Try moConnection = New System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection(ConnectionString) moConnection.Open() Success = True Catch ex As System.Exception Message = ex.Message End Try Else Success = True End If

stage.name: Execute
stage.code:
Dim oCommand As System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand
Success = False Message = ""
Try oCommand = New System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand oCommand.Connection = moConnection oCommand.CommandType = System.Data.CommandType.Text oCommand.CommandText = SQL
If Not moTransaction Is Nothing Then oCommand.Transaction = moTransaction End If
Records_Affected = CDec(oCommand.ExecuteNonQuery) Success = True
Catch ex As System.Exception Message = ex.Message End Try

stage.name: Close
stage.code:
Success = False Message = ""
If moConnection Is Nothing Then Success = True Else Try moConnection.Close() moConnection.Dispose() moConnection = Nothing Success = True Catch ex As System.Exception Message = ex.Message End Try End If

stage.name: Execute Return Number
stage.code:
Dim oCommand As System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand
Success = False Message = ""
Try oCommand = New System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand oCommand.Connection = moConnection oCommand.CommandType = System.Data.CommandType.Text oCommand.CommandText = SQL Result = CDec(oCommand.ExecuteScalar) Success = True
Catch ex As System.Exception Message = ex.Message End Try

stage.name: Execute Return Text
stage.code:
Dim oCommand As System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand
Success = False Message = ""
Try oCommand = New System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand oCommand.Connection = moConnection oCommand.CommandType = System.Data.CommandType.Text oCommand.CommandText = SQL Result = CStr(oCommand.ExecuteScalar) Success = True
Catch ex As System.Exception Message = ex.Message End Try

stage.name: Begin Transaction
stage.code:
Success = False Message = ""
If Not moConnection Is Nothing AndAlso moConnection.State = System.Data.ConnectionState.Open Then Try moTransaction = moConnection.BeginTransaction() Success = True Catch ex As System.Exception Message = ex.Message End Try End If

stage.name: Commit Transaction
stage.code:
Success = False Message = ""
Try If Not moTransaction Is Nothing Then moTransaction.Commit() moTransaction = Nothing End If
Success = True Catch ex As System.Exception Message = ex.Message End Try

stage.name: Rollback Transaction
stage.code:
Success = False Message = ""
Try If Not moTransaction Is Nothing Then moTransaction.Rollback() moTransaction = Nothing End If
Success = True Catch ex As System.Exception Message = ex.Message End Try

stage.name: Get Data Table
stage.code:
Dim oCommand As System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand Dim oDataAdapter As System.Data.SqlClient.SqlDataAdapter Dim oDataSet As System.Data.DataSet
Success = False Message = ""
Try oCommand = New System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand oCommand.Connection = moConnection oCommand.CommandType = System.Data.CommandType.Text oCommand.CommandText = SQL
oDataAdapter = New System.Data.SqlClient.SqlDataAdapter oDataAdapter .SelectCommand = oCommand oDataset = New System.Data.DataSet oDataAdapter.Fill(oDataset) Results = oDataSet.Tables(0) Success = True
Catch ex As System.Exception Message = ex.Message End Try
